README.md

# Tool & System Installation Guidelines

## System Requirements (Pre-Check)

Before installing tools, ensure your machine meets these specs:

| Component | Minimum Requirement |
| RAM | 6 GB |
| HDD / Disk Space | 50 GB free space |
| CPU | 4 virtual CPU cores (4 vCPU) |
| Operating System | Ubuntu 20.04 |

---

## Tools to Install

1. **Yosys** (HDL synthesis tool)  
   ```bash
   sudo apt-get update
   git clone https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys.git
   cd yosys
   sudo apt install make    
   sudo apt-get install build-essential clang bison flex \
       libreadline-dev gawk tcl-dev libffi-dev git \
       graphviz xdot pkg-config python3 libboost-system-dev \
       libboost-python-dev libboost-filesystem-dev zlib1g-dev
   make config-gcc
   make
   sudo make install

2. Iverilog

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install iverilog


3. GTKWave (Waveform Viewer)

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt install gtkwave


4. ngspice

Source tarball download : https://sourceforge.net/projects/ngspice/files/

Extract and build:


tar -zxvf ngspice-37.tar.gz
cd ngspice-37
mkdir release
cd release
../configure --with-x --with-readline=yes --disable-debug
make
sudo make install


5. Magic (VLSI layout tool)

sudo apt-get install m4
sudo apt-get install tcsh
sudo apt-get install csh
sudo apt-get install libx11-dev
sudo apt-get install tcl-dev tk-dev
sudo apt-get install libcairo2-dev
sudo apt-get install mesa-common-dev libglu1-mesa-dev
sudo apt-get install libncurses-dev
git clone https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/magic
cd magic
./configure
make
sudo make install


6. OpenLane

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade
sudo apt install -y build-essential python3 python3-venv python3-pip make git sudo apt install apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl software-properties-common
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg
echo "deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
sudo docker run hello-world
sudo groupadd docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
sudo reboot
# Reboot ke baad:
docker run hello-world

# Phir:
cd $HOME
git clone https://github.com/The-OpenROAD-Project/OpenLane
cd OpenLane
make
make test



